        <dc:title>Beyond the Box: B.F. Skinner's Technology of Behaviour from Laboratory to Life, 1950s-1970s</dc:title>
        <dcterms:abstract>Beyond the Box is the first full-length study of the ways in which Skinner's ideas left the laboratory to become part of the post-war public's everyday lives, and chronicles both the enthusiasm and caution with which this process was received.</dcterms:abstract>
